    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate is anchored by the elite 86.57 rating for **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who benefits significantly from a favorable park factor and a matchup against a left-handed arm in Jacob Lopez. While most of our lineup faces right-handed starters, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains our most bankable asset, showing high offensive efficiency regardless of handedness. On the other end of the spectrum, **Lawrence Butler** (66.81) and **Will Smith** (66.36) offer excellent value despite lower lineup spots, with **Lawrence Butler** specifically thriving thanks to a 13% platoon boost against righty Slade Cecconi. While **Geraldo Perdomo** (63.70) is in a tough spot against the high-velocity Imanaga, his move to the #2 hole provides just enough projected volume to justify the start in our utility slot.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the team today was keeping **Matt Chapman** (46.03) on the bench. He hovered near the cut line, but his efficiency was dragged down by the matchup against Griffin Jax, whose 3.01 xERA serves as a significant hurdle. Although **Matt Chapman** has the benefit of the #2 spot, the optimizer favored the higher volatility/upside of **Gavin Sheets** and **Wenceel Perez**\u2014the latter being included specifically for his 100% stolen base profile. We must monitor the official lineups closely; should anyone like **Tyler Freeman** be shifted further down the order against Chris Sale, we may need to pivot to our bench depth to ensure we are maximizing our limited game caps. Risk remains elevated across the board due to \"Lineup Pending\" status for nearly every slot, so stay alert for any late-breaking changes that could impact the situational advantages currently favoring **Cal Raleigh** and **Jonathan Aranda**.",
